{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource cleanup in OPT termination function\n\n### Summary\nThe `terminate_opt()` function in the OPT module had several resource cleanup issues that could lead to resource leaks and undefined behavior when terminating the OPT tracing system.\n\nSpecifically:\n1. The listener thread was cancelled but not properly joined, leaving it in an undefined state\n2. The listener socket was not closed when using OPT_WIRESHARK mode with localhost\n3. No null checks were performed before closing file descriptors and sockets\n4. Global state variables were not reset, potentially causing issues on re-initialization\n\nThis fix ensures proper cleanup of all resources and graceful termination of threads.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OPT/probe.c`: \n  - Initialize `opt_listener.sd` to -1 for proper detection of active sockets\n  - Add proper thread termination with `pthread_join()` after `pthread_cancel()`\n  - Add cleanup of listener socket in termination function\n  - Add null/validity checks before closing resources\n  - Reset global state variables (`opt_type` and `opt_enabled`) at end of function\n\n"
}